cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a fully homomorphic crypto-processor and its security against physical or software-based attacks. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the hardware design of the processor. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper mentions the processor running OpenRISC standard machine code. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses running encrypted machine code on encrypted data. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the processor's architecture and its two distinct modes of operation.
